  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Input Forms</title>

    <para role="TEXT">This section gives detailed descriptions of the input forms
    displayed by the <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Swap"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module.</para>

    <section condition="TITLE=Swap - Initiation;PERM=sw_access;ACCESS=SW_01"
             id="SW_sw_initiation_form" role="TOPIC">
      <title>New Swap Form</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This form is displayed by the functions for creating a new Swap
      request, which are found in the <guisubmenu>Enter Swap</guisubmenu> part
      of the <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Swap"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module menu; for example
      the <guimenuitem>New Trade</guimenuitem> function.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">??????? Andra - I've included the following as an example of the
      format used for describing on-screen forms. It's mostly tables of field
      descriptions, in subsections corresponding to the sections in the
      screen. But please don't feel you have to stick strictly to this format
      - improvements to it it would be welcome. (This example comes from the
      Loan module of Misys Portal, and will obviously need to be deleted
      before we insert a real form description.) ?????????????????</para>

